This past Friday, @johnnylupes and I had some time to spare before linking up with friends from out of town. We explored the exterior of the Ponce de Leon Hotel, the centerpiece of Flagler College, and found some buttery light shining through one of the many archways. I didn't capture it here, but the Spanish Colonial architecture is incredibly unique relative to what you typically see here in the US. I'll have to incorporate it into some upcoming photography. I'm delighted with my new home, and optimistic about the rest of 2023.
